  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study tests preschoolers, school children, youths and young adults, who were born
      preterm or full-term, in their theory of mind abilities.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Is there any difference in the development of theory of mind between preterms and full-terms?
      Is there a risk group of preterms to develop a deficit in theroy of mind?

      Four groups are tested: prescoolers (again two years later), youths and young adults.

      All participants were tested for theory of mind, executive functions, language and cognitive
      abilites.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
